  "doc_id": "2753",
  "text": "OFFIS. OFFIS is a system designed to facilitate an interactive and iterative office analysis and design process, providing the planner/designer of the automated office with a flexible method for analyzing system features and constraints [CITATION_1] . OFFIS was developed at the Department of Management Information Systems at the University of Arizona. The system is based on the OFFIS model. The elements of the model can be specified in the OFFIS language by planners/ designers who are office personnel or managers. The language has a simple syntax and is nonprocedural.",
  "correct_citation": {
